From 9414dec24bbb36c0aed6e7365d9b5041b52a9e43 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 11:23:39 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] InputMethodManager: stop intercepting KEYCODE_SYM for picker

Stock InputMethodManager.dispatchInputEvent intercepts ACTION_DOWN on
KEYCODE_SYM with repeatCount == 0 and calls showInputMethodPickerLocked
to bring up the language / IME switcher. The hijack happens BEFORE the
event reaches the active IME, so the IME never sees the key.

On the MP01 the dedicated hardware SYM key (scancode 249) is consumed
by Pastiera (the only IME shipped on this build) to toggle its inline
symbols / emoji / clipboard pages. With the stock interception in
place, every press of the SYM key just opens a one-item input-method
picker and Pastiera's symbols panel is unreachable.

Drop the four-line interception so the SYM key flows through to the
IME normally. Single-IME builds lose nothing (the picker has no
choices to make). Multi-IME users can still switch via
Settings > System > Languages or via the IME's own UI.

Change-Id: I97416dad3dc646883207b5509f4ee02817cd49b2
---
 .../view/inputmethod/InputMethodManager.java  | 19 ++++++++++---------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/core/java/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodManager.java b/core/java/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodManager.java
index f6c61140201e..7868e7a3a179 100644
--- a/core/java/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodManager.java
+++ b/core/java/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodManager.java
@@ -4352,15 +4352,16 @@ public final class InputMethodManager {
             FinishedInputEventCallback callback, Handler handler) {
         synchronized (mH) {
             if (isImeSessionAvailableLocked()) {
-                if (event instanceof KeyEvent) {
-                    KeyEvent keyEvent = (KeyEvent)event;
-                    if (keyEvent.getAction() == KeyEvent.ACTION_DOWN
-                            && keyEvent.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.KEYCODE_SYM
-                            && keyEvent.getRepeatCount() == 0) {
-                        showInputMethodPickerLocked();
-                        return DISPATCH_HANDLED;
-                    }
-                }
+                // E-Ink / MP01: drop the stock SYM-as-input-method-picker shortcut.
+                // The MP01's hardware SYM key is consumed by Pastiera (the only
+                // IME shipped on this build) to flip its inline symbols / emoji
+                // pages. Stock IMM intercepts KEYCODE_SYM on ACTION_DOWN and
+                // shows the input-method picker, swallowing the event before
+                // the IME ever sees it. Since we ship a single IME and the
+                // user isn't switching languages from this key, just let the
+                // event flow through to Pastiera. (If a multi-IME setup is
+                // needed in the future, switch via Settings > Languages.)
+
 
                 if (android.tracing.Flags.imetrackerProtolog()) {
                     ProtoLog.v(INPUT_METHOD_MANAGER_DEBUG, "DISPATCH INPUT EVENT: %s",
